Hello golang-dev@googlegroups.com,

I'd like you to review this change to
https://code.google.com/p/go

R=close

Not worth it. Doesn't even show up in godoc, and http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_number#Notation says that both notations are used.

On 2013/06/05 20:51:23, bradfitz wrote:
> R=close
> 
> Not worth it. Doesn't even show up in godoc, and
> http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_number#Notation says that both notations
> are used.

Are both 2+3i and 4+i5 allowed as input? If not, why would we show them as an output?

It's an internal comment, not output. Look at CL first.
